<p>
  This option is used to get the raw data that matches your filters (as opposed to aggregating the data). You can choose to get all the fields in your data or select the particular few you are interested in from them.
</p>

<h6 class="content-sub-header">Show All Fields</h6>
<p>
  If selected, all fields  are displayed in the output. The Result Page will be shown as the raw JSON view by default.
</p>
<h6 class="content-sub-header">Select Fields</h6>
<p>
  If selected, only the selected fields are displayed in the output. You can optionally rename each fields, which can be useful if many fields are extracted and you are viewing the data in a tabular mode.  The Result Page will be shown as the table view by default.
</p>

<h5 class="content-header">Maximum Record Count</h5>
<p>
  For Raw Data queries, you can also provide a maximum record count below in the Query Stop Criteria. Bullet can return the data when this count is reached even if your Maximum Duration has not been reached.
</p>
